In general `net_pack_*` methods are OK for little-endian systems.
If one decide to optimize big-endian case, it will be impossible due to `net_pack_*` interface itself - you use `uint8_t *` type and loose original value type. Did you consider smth like this?
```
size_t net_pack_u32(uint32_t *value, uint32_t v)
{
#ifndef WORDS_BIGENDIAN
    uint8_t *p = (uint8_t *)value;
    p += net_pack_u16(p, (v >> 16) & 0xffff);
    p += net_pack_u16(p, v & 0xffff);
    return p - value;
#elif
    *value = v;
    return sizeof(v);
#endif
}
```
